‚úÖ Best Way: Use useMutation from TanStack Query

Since refetch() in useQuery runs on page load, it‚Äôs not the best choice. Instead, useMutation is the best solution because it runs only when triggered manually (e.g., on logout click).


---

üî• Solution: Use useMutation in Logout.tsx

We will use useMutation to fetch the CSRF token only before logout.

‚úÖ Step 1: Update useCsrfToken.ts to Use useMutation

import { useMutation } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import axios from 'axios';

export function useCsrfToken() {
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: async () => {
      const response = await axios.get('/secure/api/csrf-token', { withCredentials: true });
      return response.data;
    },
  });
}


---

‚úÖ Step 2: Update Logout.tsx to Call CSRF Token Before Logout

export default function Logout() {
  const { data: uiConfigData } = useUiConfigData();
  const csrfMutation = useCsrfToken(); // ‚úÖ Use mutation hook

  if (!uiConfigData) return <p>Error loading UI config data</p>;

  const handleLogout = async () => {
    const baseUrl = uiConfigData?.baseSlalUrl;

    try {
      // ‚úÖ Fetch CSRF token before logout
      const { data: csrfToken } = await csrfMutation.mutateAsync();

      // ‚úÖ Redirect to logout API with CSRF token
      window.location.href = `${baseUrl}/secure/customer-platform/logout?CSRF_TOKEN=${csrfToken}`;
    } catch (error) {
      console.error('Failed to fetch CSRF token before logout:', error);
    }
  };

  return (
    <HStack itemCenter>
      <Button variant="flat" action="primary" onPress={handleLogout}>
        <Button.Icon as={IconLogout} />
        <Button.Text>Logout</Button.Text>
      </Button>
    </HStack>
  );
}


---

üéØ Why This Works

‚úÖ useMutation runs only when manually triggered (no auto-fetch on page load).
‚úÖ Ensures fresh CSRF token is fetched just before logout.
‚úÖ No unnecessary API calls.
‚úÖ TanStack Query is still used efficiently.

This is the best solution that keeps your CSRF logic inside TanStack Query while preventing unnecessary refetching on page load. üöÄ‚úÖ


